# AI Image Processing SaaS ‚Äî Project Overview

## What This App Does
A SaaS platform for AI-powered image enhancement. Users upload images and select a processing mode:
- **Upscale** ‚Äî increase resolution up to 16x (max ~512MP)
- **Enhance** ‚Äî improve detail, color, and lighting
- **Sharpen** ‚Äî fix soft or out-of-focus images
- **Denoise** ‚Äî reduce grain and noise
- **Restore** ‚Äî repair old photos, scans, and vintage images
- **Face Enhancement** ‚Äî boost facial detail
- **Remove Background** ‚Äî automatic background removal

Processing is **async** (jobs run on a background queue). Users pay via credits.

## Tech Stack
- **Next.js** (App Router, React Server Components, React 19)
- **TypeScript** (strict mode, no `any`)
- **Tailwind CSS v4** (CSS-first, no config file ‚Äî config is in `src/styles/global.css`)
- **Drizzle ORM** + **PostgreSQL** (PGlite in local dev)
- **Clerk** ‚Äî authentication; **public `/pricing`** embeds Clerk Billing `<PricingTable />` (plans configured in Clerk Dashboard, not hard-coded in the app)
- **next-intl** ‚Äî i18n (locales: `en`, `fr`)
- **Arcjet** ‚Äî security / bot protection (in middleware)
- **Sentry** + **PostHog** + **LogTape** ‚Äî observability
- **Zod** ‚Äî validation; **React Hook Form** ‚Äî forms
- **Vitest** (unit/component) + **Playwright** (integration/E2E)

## Key Architecture
- All routes live under `src/app/[locale]/`
- **Page UI** ‚Äî feature-specific components live under `src/components/pages/<area>/...` (e.g. `boost/enhance-image`, `marketing`, `pricing-plans`); route `page.tsx` files compose them and stay small
- Route groups: `(auth)` for protected pages, `(marketing)` for public landing + pricing
- Image upload ‚Üí job created in DB ‚Üí background processor picks up ‚Üí result stored ‚Üí user notified
- Middleware = `src/proxy.ts` (NOT `middleware.ts`) ‚Äî keeps bundle small
- Env vars MUST go through `src/libs/core/Env.ts` ‚Äî never read `process.env` directly in app code
- DB singleton in `src/libs/core/DB.ts` ‚Äî avoids duplicate pool connections during HMR
- All user-visible strings must use `next-intl` translations

## Domain Concepts
- **Job** ‚Äî a single image processing task with status: `pending | processing | completed | failed`
- **Credit** ‚Äî unit of usage; each job costs credits based on operation type and output size
- **Operation** ‚Äî one of: `upscale`, `enhance`, `sharpen`, `denoise`, `restore`, `face_enhance`, `remove_bg`
- **User** ‚Äî authenticated via Clerk; has a credit balance tracked in DB

## Core Principles
- Clarity and consistency over cleverness
- Match existing patterns ‚Äî minimal surface-area changes
- Named exports only (no default exports except Next.js pages/layouts)
- Absolute imports via `@/` unless same directory (use `./foo` then)
- `type` over `interface` everywhere
